---
title: Chopped Chicken Salad with Charred Veggies and Avocado-Lime Dressing
description: Velvety avocado creates a delicious (and healthy!) base for this creamy dressing. Spiced chicken is paired with slightly charred peppers and onions to take this chopped chicken salad to the next level.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chopped-romaine-salad-with-avocado-crema-8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chopped-chicken-salad-8b4567.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chopped-chicken-salad-571542774dab71fa338b4567
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 464 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 27 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 116 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and slice the @red onion{1} into wedges. Core, seed, and thinly slice the @red bell pepper{1}. Toss the peppers and the onions on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for ~{20%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking.

Sear the chicken: Season the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} on all sides with the @Southwest spice blend{1%teaspoon}, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, and @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over high heat. Sear the chicken for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, then transfer to the baking sheet in the oven for ~{8-10%minutes}, until cooked through.

Core and dice the @Roma tomato{1}. Pick the @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves, then finely chop the stems. Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Slice the @Romaine lettuce{1} into ½-inch pieces and place in a large #bowl{}.

Halve, pit, and cube the @avocado{1}. Place half in a medium bowl with the lime zest, cilantro stems, and the juice of half a lime. Mash together with a #fork{} until completely smooth. Mix in @sour cream{2%tablespoon}. Season with salt, pepper, and additional lime juice, if needed.

Heat the broiler to high or the oven to 500 degrees. Cook the chicken and veggies for an additional ~{2-3%minutes}, until they are slightly charred. Toss the charred veggies into the romaine lettuce along with the tomatoes, cilantro leaves, and cubed avocado. Stir the avocado-lime dressing into the salad and toss until evenly coated. Thinly slice the chicken.

Plate and serve: Serve the chopped salad topped with the sliced chicken and enjoy!